    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>NGC 3256 is a nearby (35 Mpc) late stage merger between two gas rich spiral galaxies.  We propose to observe NGC 3256 in HCN J=1-0 and HCO+ J=1-0 (PI: Sakamoto), both of which trace dense molecular gas. With these observations, we will study the distribution and quantity of dense molecular gas within NGC 3256. Using ALMA Cycle 0 observations of CO J=1-0 (PI: Sakamoto), we will determine the dense gas fraction in NGC 3256, including any variations in the fraction. As a secondary goal, we will attempt to detect HNC J=1-0, another dense gas tracer. The remaining bands will be used to study free-free continuum emission. Finally, these observations will be compared to Cycle 1 observations of the early stage merger NGC 4038/39 (PI: Schirm) to study how dense molecular gas and star formation varies from early to late stage merger.</prp:abstract>
